	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Also the FX chip wasn't the only special chip. The DSP chip for example was in alot of classics like pilot wings and mario cart. The SA-1 Chip was also in the Kirby games and Mario RPG, and the C4 chip was in the later Megaman X games. Streetfighter Alpha 2 and Star Ocean had a chip called S-DDP which was just a decompression chip. It was cheaper than adding more ROM space. Most of these games except for pilot wings and mario kart are 2D. And those just use the DSP chip for enhanced mode 7 which isn't true 3D anyway. 
<br />
<br />Also, Doom used the FX chip and it wasn't bad. It wasn't the greatest but it was a decent port for a 16 bit system.

		

		</td>
